question: Kenneth and Matt have 133 minutes to walk to the library together. It takes them 11 minutes to get to the corner where the bank is. It takes them another 58 minutes to get to the park. How much longer do they have to get to library without being late?
answer:
Kenneth and Matt arrive at the bank with 133 - 11 = <<133-11=122>>122 minutes left to reach the park.
They then arrive at the park and have 122 - 58 = <<122-58=64>>64 minutes left to get to library without being late.
#### 64
